another is white; the third is striped.<br /><br />One pair of pants is white; the other is blue.<br /><br />If you reach into the closet without looking and pull out one shirt and one pair of pants, what is the probability that you will select the striped shirt and the white pants?<br /><br />That is, find P(striped shirt and white pants).<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><img alt=\"An illustration of the 3 shirts and 2 pairs of pants in your closet.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"5"},"leftText":"<p>Count the total ways to make an outfit.<br /><br />With each shirt, you could select either pair of pants.<br /><br />You can make a total of 6 outfits.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
